<p>Run this comparison monthly. Track trends over time.</p>
<h3>5C. Analyze What Competitors Do Differently</h3>
<p>For queries where competitors get cited and you do not, visit the competitor's cited page. Analyze:
- How is their content structured?
- Do they have FAQ sections?
- Do they include original data or statistics?
- Is their page more recently updated?
- Do they have better schema markup?</p>
<p>The answers tell you what to fix on your own content.</p>
<p>For more on analyzing competitors, see our guide on <a href="/blog/analyze-competitor-keywords/">competitive keyword analysis</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> AI visibility is a zero-sum game for brand mentions. If an AI engine recommends 3 brands per answer, your goal is to be one of them. Competitive tracking tells you who you need to displace.</p>
